\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Longsleeved T-shirt flattening in simulation: per-horizon performance of learning-based single-arm pick-and-place (\text  {PnP}) controllers. For each metric (Normalised Coverage, Normalised Improvement, Max IoU, and Success Rate), the columns report the cumulative \emph  {Max} (best value reached within the horizon) and the \emph  {Last} (final-step) value at 5, 10, 20, and 30 action steps; cell colour encodes the score in $[0,1]$. We enable only the single-arm PnP primitive of the off-the-shelf \text  {ClothFunnels}~\cite  {canberk2023cloth} to keep a consistent environment; \text  {PlaNet-ClothPick} and \text  {LaGarNet} use the RGB-to-Mask setup on the same task-focused and all-garment datasets with their own reward functions, while \text  {Diffusion Policy}~\cite  {kadi2025draper, chi2023diffusionpolicy} is trained on 200 human demonstrations. The state-of-the-art mesh-based planner \text  {MEDOR}~\cite  {huang2022mesh} is evaluated with its own simulation setup. Our All-Garments \text  {LaGarNet} reaches performance comparable to MEDOR and closely matches human experts (and slightly exceeds them at 10--20 steps); the small Max$\to $Last gap indicates that final configurations remain stable.}}{10}{figure.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:longsleeve-flattening}{{5}{10}{Longsleeved T-shirt flattening in simulation: per-horizon performance of learning-based single-arm pick-and-place (\text {PnP}) controllers. For each metric (Normalised Coverage, Normalised Improvement, Max IoU, and Success Rate), the columns report the cumulative \emph {Max} (best value reached within the horizon) and the \emph {Last} (final-step) value at 5, 10, 20, and 30 action steps; cell colour encodes the score in $[0,1]$. We enable only the single-arm PnP primitive of the off-the-shelf \text {ClothFunnels}~\cite {canberk2023cloth} to keep a consistent environment; \text {PlaNet-ClothPick} and \text {LaGarNet} use the RGB-to-Mask setup on the same task-focused and all-garment datasets with their own reward functions, while \text {Diffusion Policy}~\cite {kadi2025draper, chi2023diffusionpolicy} is trained on 200 human demonstrations. The state-of-the-art mesh-based planner \text {MEDOR}~\cite {huang2022mesh} is evaluated with its own simulation setup. Our All-Garments \text {LaGarNet} reaches performance comparable to MEDOR and closely matches human experts (and slightly exceeds them at 10--20 steps); the small Max$\to $Last gap indicates that final configurations remain stable}{figure.caption.8}{}}
\newlabel{fig:longsleeve-flattening@cref}{{[figure][5][]5}{[1][9][]10}}
