\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {III}{\ignorespaces Secondary comparison of computational requirements and data efficiency across garment flattening baselines. $\dagger $ represents the reported values in the original paper. \text  {ClothFunnels} uses a machine with 4 NVIDIA RTX3090s. Our hardware setup for all timing and parameter evaluations is: Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS, NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3090 Ti GPU, AMD Ryzen 9 5900X 12-Core Processor (2 threads per core), and 64GB RAM. Whist mesh-based method requires substantially shorter data collection time, our LaGarNet method demands much less network parameters and faster training and per-step inference time.}}{12}{table.caption.10}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:efficiency-comparison}{{III}{12}{Secondary comparison of computational requirements and data efficiency across garment flattening baselines. $\dagger $ represents the reported values in the original paper. \text {ClothFunnels} uses a machine with 4 NVIDIA RTX3090s. Our hardware setup for all timing and parameter evaluations is: Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS, NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3090 Ti GPU, AMD Ryzen 9 5900X 12-Core Processor (2 threads per core), and 64GB RAM. Whist mesh-based method requires substantially shorter data collection time, our LaGarNet method demands much less network parameters and faster training and per-step inference time}{table.caption.10}{}}
